replies.body:
Meddler the problem is, now, that games snowball too quickly and it is harder to reach late game, plus the nerfs on general AS and buffing crit, he stands on a middle ground, because Draven is a champ that scales real hard in this order AD - CRIT - ARMOR PEN - AS.

You can obtain an item that grants AD and Crit: {{item:3031}} 
But you can't obtain an item that grants AD, Crit and Armor Pen: the old {{item:3142}} 
Actually you could just solve his win ratio issue by taking a look at wich items you are recommending on him:

He would benefit more of {{item:3078}} in a midgame than a {{item:3087}} or a {{item:3094}} 
You should also consider to test if adding 5% more critical into the math of the {{item:3078}} could help.
Right now the only 2 things that scale in this item (in terms of stats) is the HP and the AD from the {{item:3044}}. LITERALLY, the upgrade only means 10 more AD and 50 HP, which is 450 gold worth that you are paying for, and the stat upgrade.
It could at least use a buff towards 5% crit and 5% AS by making it cost 200 more gold, because if we are already paying 3800 gold for this, I wouldn't mind to pay 200 more knowing that it will be better.

ALSO: adding {{item:3147}} to his recommended build could solve a lot.

And he could take benefit of this item finally being included on the rift: {{item:3185}} (reworked, new icon, but keeping the AD-Crit-Bleed relation).

Because being honest, he doesn't take too much adavantage of building AS, with 40-50% he is ok, so that he can catch his 2 axes and keep attacking.

Just a recommendation.

{{sticker:slayer-jinx-catface}}
